                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1223">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Turkey/375: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-23T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 23, 1943—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>253. Your 387, March 2, 1 p.m. Terms of transportation agreement appear highly
                    constructive.</p>
                <p>In light of your paragraph 2, the Department and BEW concur in your decision not
                    to press for inspection privileges at Guleman.</p>
                <p>With respect to your paragraph 3, the Department will bear in mind advisability
                    of direct communication with London in the later event that prompt action on
                    price is indicated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
